{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "Implemented the segmented writing engine and checkpointed it in commit `7748dd6` (`feat(prompt-61): segmented writing engine`). The backend now writes one outline-card segment at a time, carries forward structured `accepted_summary` cont...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_197", "text": "Implemented the segmented writing engine and checkpointed it in commit `7748dd6` (`feat(prompt-61): segmented writing engine`). The backend now writes one outline-card segment at a time, carries forward structured `accepted_summary` context instead of replaying the full draft, persists `raw_generated_text` / `accepted_text` / `accepted_summary`, and compiles the final story from the latest accepted revision of each segment index so rewrites stay isolated.\n\nVerification completed with `python -m compileall`, targeted pytest (`34 passed`), `make backend-format-check`, targeted `ruff check`, `make backend-test` (`218 passed, 5 skipped`), and `make backend-integration-test` (`5 passed`). No browser or screenshot checks were run because this prompt only changed backend orchestration/persistence. The required reviewer summary was written last at [summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.yolopilot/runs/20260331T205548_storyteller_prompt_pack/61_segmented_writing_engine/summary.md).", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 390, "prompt_index": 62, "prompt_name": "61 \u2014 Segmented Writing Engine", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-02T07:20:40-07:00"}
